+## Security
+
+These workflows run an autonomous agent with repository write access and your
+`CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN`. On a **public** repo, treat every PR diff and
+PR/issue/comment as untrusted. The workflows enforce a trust model so untrusted
+actors cannot drive the privileged jobs:
+
+- `/claude-review` and `/claude-fix` comment triggers run only for repo
+  maintainers (`OWNER`/`MEMBER`/`COLLABORATOR`).
+- The auto PR-review path runs only for same-repo (non-fork) branches.
+- Whether the auto-fix runs is decided only from the review step's own output,
+  never from attacker-writable comments or issues, and fails closed.
+- Third-party actions are pinned to commit SHAs and kept patched by Dependabot.
+
+Read **[SECURITY.md](SECURITY.md)** for the full threat model and the
+recommended required-reviewer Environment hardening before enabling auto-fix on
+a public repository.
+
